devdoc.details: Once the contract is compile and deployed, use the following to run functions from command line1. let charity;2. CryptoDonater.at("0xA8a51239A735a6BA00d20e282d2A56Eae5439191").then(function(x) { charity = x });3. Then run the corresponding command for function of your choice (see @dev for each function below)

createCategory(string,uint256).details: Use the following from command line to call this functioncharity.createCategory("Logistics Costs", 200).then(function(x) { return x; });

getCatListLength().details: Use the following from command line to call this functioncharity.getCatListLength().then(function(x) { return x; });

getCatValues(uint256).details: Use the following from command line to call this functioncharity.getCatValues(2).then(function(x) { return x; });

getLatestPrice().details: Use the following from command line to call this functioncharity.getLatestPrice().then(function(x) { return x; });

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

sendDonation(uint256).details: Use the following from command line to call this functioncharity.sendDonation(1).then(function(x) { return x; });

params.catId: of the category pool. Txn should also have 'from' and 'value'.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
